The paper focuses on image clustering using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a deep convolutional autoencoder (CAE) and applying density-based clustering algorithms, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using t-SNE for dimensionality reduction, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
